<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL; BATISTE SPARKS LONG BEACH WILSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Batiste scored the game's last five points and had a key block in the 
last minute to lead Long Beach Wilson to 65-58 upset of 12th-ranked Los 
Alamitos in a Division I-AA Southern Section quarterfinal game Tuesday night at 
Huntington Beach High. 
</P>
<P>
 Batiste finished with a game-high 30 points and a 10 rebounds for Wilson, 
22-7. Los Alamitos finished at 22-5. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 1 Santa Ana Mater Dei 70, Valley View of Moreno Valley 44 -- Miles Simon 
scored 21 points to lead Mater Dei (29-0) to a Division I-A quarterfinal 
victory over Valley View (17-9) at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 3 Compton Dominguez 78, Westlake 52 -- Jamie Gillins scored 21 points to 
lead Dominguez (25-2) to a Division II-A second-round victory at Westlake 
(17-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 85, No. 4 Fontana 77 -- Brock Jacobsen scored 33 points, 
including five three-pointers, to lead Crescenta Valley (17-8) to an upset over 
Fontana (26-2) in a Division I-AA quarterfinal game at Glendale College. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley outscored Fontana, 20-7, in the second quarter to take a 
34-25 lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 6 Inglewood 70, Compton 45 -- Paul Pierce scored 22 points to lead 
Inglewood (25-3) to a Division II-AA second-round victory at Compton (15-12). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 8 Bellflower St. John Bosco 68, La Mirada 42 -- St. John Bosco went on a 
20-2 run to take a 38-18 halftime lead and held on for a Division II-A 
second-round victory over La Mirada (17-10) at Biola College. 
</P>
<P>
 St. John Bosco (25-2) was led by Jelani Gardner's 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 10 Long Beach Poly 50, Fountain Valley 48 -- James Brown took an 
off-balance shot from the top of the key that rolled around the rim and went in 
at the buzzer to give Poly (23-6) a victory over Fountain Valley (23-6) in a 
Division I-AA quarterfinal game at at Edison High. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 14 Loyola 91, No. 19 Downey Warren 78 -- Toby Bailey scored 36 points to 
lead Loyola (22-5) over Warren (22-7) in a Division I-A quarterfinal game at 
Downey High. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 16 Santa Ana Valley 68, Chino Hills Ayala 64 -- Santa Ana Valley (26-3) 
watched a 21-point, third-quarter lead slip away, but held on for a victory 
over Ayala (22-5) in a Division I-AA quarterfinal game at Century High. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 17 Glendora 58, Huntington Beach Ocean View 53 -- Cameron Murray scored 30 
points to lead Glendora (26-2) in a Division II-AA second-round victory at 
Ocean View (14-14). 
</P>
<P>
 In other games: Marcus Lemmons scored 19 points to lead Gahr to a 52-41 
victory over Agoura (18-8) in a Division II-AA second-round game at Gahr 
(18-10). . . . Robert Lutes scored 20 points to lead Palm Desert (15-10) to a 
72-58 victory over Riverside Poly (18-10) in a Division II-AA second-round game 
at Palm Desert. 
</P>
<P>
 Shane Willis scored 27 points to lead Mira Costa to a 64-44 victory over Paso 
Robles (19-6) in a Division II-A second-round game at Mira Costa (22-6). . . . 
Duane Curtis scored 23 points for Muir (19-11) in a 78-50 victory over Temple 
City (14-12) in a Division II-A second-round game at Temple City. 
</P>
