</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nancy Kerrigan has signed a contract with the Walt Disney Co. that includes a 
TV story of her life, a children's book and appearances at Disney theme parks. 
</P>
<P>
 The deal, its value undisclosed, is not contingent on Kerrigan's winning a 
medal at the Winter Olympics, said Greg Taylor, a spokesman for Walt Disney 
Television. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tonya Harding's former husband, Jeff Gillooly, was denied permission to go to 
Colorado to testify against her at a disciplinary hearing by the U.S. Figure 
Skating Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Circuit Judge Donald Londer refused request that he be allowed to go to 
Colorado Springs for the March 9 hearing, a ruling that angered the prosecutor 
and surprised the attorney for the USFSA. 
</P>
<P>
 The USFSA had asked that Gillooly appear at the hearing, which will consider 
whether Harding violated the association's code of ethics by her actions 
surrounding the Jan. 6 attack on Kerrigan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
