<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; MARTINEZ'S 9 RBIS HELP VENTURA, 29-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman third baseman Hernan Martinez set a school record with nine runs 
batted in to lead Ventura College to a 29-3 victory over Compton on Tuesday in 
a nonconference baseball game. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez had a grand slam in the fifth inning and a three-run homer in the 
sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates (3-2) had 19 hits and benefited from eight Compton errors. The 
last 14 Ventura runs were unearned. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 7, Pierce 4 -- Rob Lanouette scattered three hits in five innings of 
relief to help Moorpark win the nonconference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Allen went two for four with two runs batted in for Moorpark (5-1-1). 
Kevin Nykoluk's solo home run in the fourth gave the Raiders a 5-1 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Sturges had two hits for Pierce (2-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 4, Valley 2 -- The Marauders (5-2) scored all their runs in 
the seventh inning of the nonconference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore right-hander Ricky Dominguez (3-0) pitched four-hitter, allowing one 
earned run. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 7, Cal Lutheran JV 0 -- Chad Olthoff (1-1) allowed three hits, struck 
out two and walked one in seven innings of the nonconference game at Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 CS Dominguez Hills 1, The Master's 0 -- Matt Davis (0-1) pitched a four-hitter 
for the Mustangs (4-5-2), but the Toros' Bert Horn gave up only two hits -- to 
Steve Smith and Matt Henzie -- in a nonconference game. 
</P>
