<TEXT>
<P>
 Intense Rivalry in Notebook Computers Heats Up: Competition in the 
fastest-growing sector of the personal computer industry intensified this week 
with Dell Computer Corp. unveiling its long-awaited notebook computer and IBM 
slashing prices on its sub-notebooks.Dell has revamped its notebook line and 
hired AST Research Inc. to make the portables under the Dell label. Wall Street 
applauded the move by the mail-order computer firm, sending Dell's stock up 
$1.75 to close at $22.75 in active Nasdaq trading. The Austin, Tex.-based 
firm's new Latitude line of machines, which weigh 5.75 to 6.4 pounds, are 
priced from $1,699 to $3,249. Meanwhile, IBM cut prices of its ThinkPad 500 
sub-notebook by up to 20%. 
</P>
