<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VOLUNTEERS TO OFFER FREE TAX ASSISTANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRENDA DAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 100 volunteers will be available free of charge to help elderly, 
disabled and low-income taxpayers file their 1993 returns at locations 
throughout Ventura County through April 15, organizers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, more than 3,500 people were assisted by the Volunteer Income Tax 
Assistance program, according to the Commission on Human Concerns, which has 
sponsored the program for 12 years. 
</P>
<P>
 This year, the commission has added automated filing, so returns can be 
expected within 10 days, organizers said. Tax help can be found at the 
following locations: 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo: Camarillo Senior Center, 1605 E. Burnley St., 10 a.m. to noon 
Mondays; Camarillo Library, 3100 Ponderosa Drive, 10 a.m. to noon Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Fillmore: St. Francis of Assisi Church, 1048 Ventura St., 10 a.m. to noon 
Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark: Catholic Charities, 77 1st St., 10 a.m. to noon Thursdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard: Oxnard Community Center, 800 Hobson Way, 10 a.m. to noon Wednesdays; 
Oxnard Library, 251 S. A St., 6:30 to 7:30 p.m. Wednesdays and Thursdays; 
Guadalupe Church, Colonia Road and Juanita Street, 6 to 8 p.m. Thursdays; 
Commission on Human Concerns, 621 Richmond Ave., 4:30 to 7 p.m. Fridays; VCCA, 
4917 S. Rose Ave., 9 a.m. to noon Mondays. 
</P>
<P>
 Port Hueneme: Prueter Library, 510 Park Ave., 5 to 7 p.m. Tuesdays; Port 
Hueneme Community Center, 550 Park Ave., 12:30 to 3:30 p.m. Tuesdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Paula: Santa Paula Nutrition Center, 530 Main St., 1 to 4 p.m. Mondays. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley: Simi Valley Senior Center, 3900 E. Avenida Simi, 9 a.m. to noon 
Mondays. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks: Goebel Senior Center, 1400 E. Janss Road, 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
Thursdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura: Santa Clara Senior Center, 420 Santa Clara St., 1 to 3 p.m. Tuesdays 
and Saturdays; Ventura Avenue Adult Center, 550 N. Ventura Ave., 9 a.m. to noon 
Tuesdays; Gregory Gardens, 9620 Telephone Road, 9 to 11 a.m. Wednesdays. BRENDA 
DAY 
</P>
