COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTY SCIENCE FAIR ENTRY DEADLINE SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County students wishing to enter the county science fair this year 
have four more weeks to complete and submit their projects. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers of the fair have set a March 18 deadline for entries to the event, 
which will be held April 19-21 at the Ventura County Fairgrounds in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by the county superintendent of schools office and the Ventura 
County Economic Development Assn., the science fair is open to students in the 
sixth through eighth grades from private and public schools throughout the 
county. 
</P>
<P>
 Students may enter either individual or group projects. Awards will be given 
in eight categories: botany; chemistry or biochemistry; earth, space and 
environmental sciences; math and computers; microbiology and medical science; 
physics; psychology, sociology and human behavior, and zoology and animal 
behavior. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call Elaine Daugherty at 388-4411. MAIA DAVIS 
