WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; SCHOOL TO HOST COMEDY BENEFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Parent-Teacher Organization of Summit School in Ojai will sponsor a comedy 
night Saturday to raise money for playground equipment at the kindergarten 
through sixth-grade school. 
</P>
<P>
 Scheduled for 7:30 to 10 p.m. at the Ojai Women's Club at 441 E. Ojai Ave., 
the fund-raiser will feature performances by two professional comedians: Jerry 
Swallow and Cary Odes.Odes' credits include televised performances at the 
Improv comedy club in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations are required for the event. Cost is $12.50 per person, including 
refreshments and a cash bar. 
</P>
<P>
 The comedy night was the idea of Parent-Teacher Organization President Valerie 
Levett, who said she is an old friend of Odes. 
</P>
<P>
 Levett asked Odes if he would perform for free at the benefit. He not only 
agreed but enlisted help from fellow comedian Swallow. 
</P>
<P>
 All the money raised at the event will go toward completing a playground at 
Summit School that the Ojai Unified School District could not afford to build. 
</P>
<P>
 The Parent-Teacher Organization has built part of the playground with a $5,000 
loan from the school district, which the organization is trying to repay. The 
parents' group needs an additional $8,000 to buy more equipment for the 
playground, Levett said. 
</P>
<P>
 To make reservations or for more information on the comedy benefit, call 
Levett at 525-2626 or Lauren Deneen at 646-2162. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
