<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UC RIVERSIDE BEATS TITANS, STOPS WINNING STREAK AT 11 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Doyle's single with two outs in the bottom of the ninth drove in Sean 
Kicherer to give host UC Riverside a 7-6 victory over Cal State Fullerton 
Tuesday. The loss stopped the Titans' 11-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton led, 6-5, entering the bottom of the ninth. Riverside had two on and 
two out when Titan relief pitcher Ted Silva struck out Dan Redington. But 
catcher Brian Loyd's passed ball allowed Redington to reach base, and after 
Silva hit third baseman Scott Laverty to tie it, 6-6, Doyle delivered the 
game-winning hit. 
</P>
<P>
 The second-ranked Titans (12-2) rallied for two runs in the ninth inning on a 
suicide squeeze by designated hitter Bret Hemphill and a sacrifice fly by Jim 
Betzsold. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Ferguson had two hits and scored two runs and Hemphill, Brian King, 
Jeremy Giambi and D.C. Olsen each had two hits each for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Doyle led Riverside (9-3), an NCAA Division II school, with two hits and two 
RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 74, Point Loma Nazarene 71 -- Danin Bryant scored 
26 points and gave out six assists for the Vanguards. Eric Carmichael added 16. 
Southern California is 15-15, 3-8.Point Loma Nazarene is 13-15, 5-6. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 8-5, Whittier 2-4 -- Lisa Simpson had a triple and a home run and Moe 
Caryl went two for three, with two RBIs and two runs scored in the first game 
for host Chapman (8-2). 
</P>
