<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: VENTURA TAKES TOP SEEDING INTO REGIONAL TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura College men's basketball team has been seeded No. 1 in the 
Southern California junior college regional tournament that starts with 
first-round games Friday and Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates (31-2), the Western State Conference North Division champions, 
will open against Harbor (13-16) Saturday at Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 In Friday games, No. 20 San Diego Mesa (15-13) visits No. 13 College of the 
Canyons (14-16), and No. 28 Oxnard (12-17) travels to No. 5 L.A. City (25-5). 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday, No. 27 Orange Coast (13-16) plays at No. 6 Moorpark (23-8), No. 
14 Antelope Valley (19-11) will play host to No. 19 Pasadena (15-15) and No. 22 
Glendale (15-14) travels to No. 11 Southwestern (24-5). 
</P>
<P>
 The women's 16-team regional tournament begins tonight with three area teams 
participating. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura (25-5), the WSC North Division champion, is seeded No. 4 and will play 
host to No. 13 Citrus (14-8). 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons (18-12), the WSC South Division winner, is seeded 14th and travels to 
No. 3 Riverside City (25-9). Oxnard (8-20), the WSC North Division runner-up, 
will visit No. 1 Golden West (29-4). FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
