<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Christina Ticsay 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Bell-Jeff 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Ticsay leads the Guards (21-5) in scoring, averaging 19.4 
points a game.She also averages six assists and three steals per game. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Ticsay, a 5-foot-7 guard, set a school record by scoring 43 
points in Bell-Jeff's victory over St. Bonaventure in a Southern Section 
Division IV-A playoff game Saturday night. Ticsay made 13 of 18 shots, 
including five three-pointers, and also had eight steals and six assists. "She 
was on fire," Coach Jim Couch said. "She could not miss." Ticsay broke the 
Bell-Jeff record of 38 points, set in 1982 by Vita Paciulli. 
</P>
