<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Al Lairson 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Palmdale 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Lairson has been perhaps the Falcons' most consistent 
player, according to Coach Garry Phelps. Lairson, who averages 15.6 points and 
5.7 rebounds a game, also was an excellent receiver on the football team. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Lairson scored 23 points and made eight of 11 shots from the 
field in Palmdale's 65-49 second-round playoff victory against Hart, which came 
into the game with a 21-1 record and a No. 1 ranking in the Times' regional 
poll. Lairson added six rebounds, three assists and three steals. The victory 
avenged one of Palmdale's three losses, a 55-52 defeat to Hart in December. 
Last week, Lairson also had 28 points and nine rebounds in Palmdale's 108-69 
victory against Temecula Valley in the first round. 
</P>
