<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA VALLEY HOLDS ON WITHOUT MANN, BEATS AYALA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Despite playing without leading scorer Olujimi Mann down the stretch, Santa 
Ana Valley beat Chino Hills Ayala, 68-64, in a Division I-AA boys' basketball 
quarterfinal game Tuesday at Century High. 
</P>
<P>
 The fourth-seeded Falcons (26-3) play Crescenta Valley, which upset top-seeded 
Fontana, in a semifinal Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons led by as many as 21 points in the third quarter, but Ayala 
rallied to within nine at the end of the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 John Holmes then opened the fourth with six consecutive points and Ayala 
trailed, 58-55. 
</P>
<P>
 Soon after, Mann fouled out with 5 minutes 53 seconds remaining and the 
Falcons leading, 60-56. Mann scored a game-high 23. 
</P>
<P>
 Ayala (22-5) took advantage of Mann's absence, scoring six consecutive points 
to take its first lead, 62-60. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Santa Ana Valley then scored its first points in more than four 
minutes when Carlos Quezada hit a three-pointer with 2:20 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 After Santa Ana Valley's Jermaine Robinson made one of two free throws, 
Holmes' steal and layup tied the score, 64-64, with 36 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Michael Riggins scored on an uncontested layup with 30 seconds 
remaining, giving Santa Ana Valley its final lead. DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
