<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUNTAIN VALLEY ELIMINATED BY A BASKET AT THE BUZZER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Long Beach Poly's James Brown took an off-balance shot from the top of the key 
that rolled around the rim and into the basket at the buzzer to give the 
Jackrabbits a 50-48 victory over Fountain Valley in the Southern Section I-AA 
boys' basketball quarterfinals Tuesday night at Edison High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown broke loose for a last ditch shot after Poly took the ball out of bounds 
with seven seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley (23-6) nursed a small lead most of the fourth quarter and led, 
48-45, on Daniel Keller's basket with 2:16 remaining. But Poly's Damon Dawson 
made a three-point play on a rebound basket and a free throw with 1:51 left to 
tie the score, 48-48, and set the stage for Brown's heroics. 
</P>
<P>
 "We did a good job defensively," Fountain Valley Coach Gordon Billingsley 
said. "We contained and slid across and helped out. We just couldn't hang on to 
our leads." 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach Poly (23-6) will play Long Beach Wilson in Friday night's 
semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 The Barons' Phil Domingo led all scorers with 18 points and teammates Keller 
and Brandon Leimbach added 13 apiece. Chris Hardy led Poly with 17 points. 
Fountain Valley shot 61.8% from the floor on 21-34 shooting. TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</TEXT>
