<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION III-A BOYS' BASKETBALL; BIG QUARTER GETS PACIFICA PAST PASADENA BLAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacifica used a 35-point third quarter and a full-court press to beat Pasadena 
Blair, 84-74, in Southern Section III-A boys' basketball quarterfinals Tuesday 
night at La Canada High School 
</P>
<P>
 Center Jon Surface was perfect from the floor in the third quarter that saw 
the Mariners (25-1) outscore Blair by nine. Surface was six for six, including 
two three-pointers and two free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing 38-34 at halftime, the Mariners tightened their full court pressure, 
which allowed Blair point guard Jecarl Riggins to score 16 first-half points 
and build the Viking lead to as much as 15 in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 After trading baskets early in the second half, Pacifica forced three 
consecutive turnovers. Surface's three-pointer and free throw tied the score, 
60-60, with 1:13 left.  
</P>
<P>
 Jaimi Bessho hit a three-pointer off the next Viking turnover to give the 
Mariners the lead for good. 
</P>
<P>
 Blair held Pacifica's Chris Vlasic to only three points. Vlasic was 1 for 10 
from the field, and didn't score a point in the Mariners' big third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Surface finished with a game-high 38 points and Erik Maurer added 11 for 
Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
 Riggins scored 31 points and Dan Cadd added 17 for Blair (18-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica will face La Canada in a semifinal game Friday at site to be 
determined. JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
