<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION DIVISION II GIRLS' SOCCER PLAYOFFS; CANYON STARTS FAST IN 4-1 
VICTORY OVER LOS ALAMITOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER STEVENS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon flattened the Los Alamitos girls' soccer team, 4-1, in the second round 
of the Southern Section Division II playoffs Tuesday at Canyon High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon, which last season lost in the Division II title game, will play 
Kennedy, a 1-0 winner over Long Beach Poly, in a quarterfinal Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Even with a four-goal lead at the half, Canyon Coach John Williams was 
nervous. "I never really felt comfortable, because Pacifica scored four times 
on Los Alamitos and lost (6-4 in the first round)." 
</P>
<P>
 Neither team had a good shot on goal until 15 minutes into the first half, 
when Laura Flatauer's attempt bounced off Griffin goalie Lynsey Salsbury, and 
Genelle Geronsin kicked it in around a group of players in front of the net. 
</P>
<P>
 The Comanches (16-5-3) scored again on a goal by Kim Nelson 19 minutes into 
the game. Nelson scored after a crossing pass from Ingrid Anderson. Three 
minutes later, Jacquie Bannister's shot from about 15 yards hit the goal post 
and Flatauer followed it up. 
</P>
<P>
 Just before the half, Krista Broughton kicked the ball over Salsbury's head 
into the net. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos (17-3-3) scored 15 minutes into the second half when Sarah Bickel 
headed in Andrea Sievers' pass. HEATHER STEVENS 
</P>
</TEXT>
