Woodbridge, but Dory believes Irvine's deep bench will help give it the edge. 
"Woodbridge has two great guys, but when depth counts, we have four good guys," 
he said. Lezak, a two-time All-American and top-four section finisher in the 
50- and 100-yard freestyles, and Ronson, the only freshman to score in two 
events at the championship meet (50 freestyle and 100 breaststroke), anchor the 
Vaqueros' hopes. 
