<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA COMMUNITY COLLEGE MEN'S BASKETBALL PAIRINGS; SEVEN ORANGE 
EMPIRE TEAMS MAKE CUT FOR THE PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Six teams from Orange County received berths in the Southern California 
community college men's basketball playoffs, which were announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside, which won the Orange Empire Conference, joins conference members 
Saddleback, Fullerton, Rancho Santiago, Irvine Valley, Cypress and Orange Coast 
in the first round of the playoffs which are Friday and Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Game times -- 7 or 7:30 p.m. -- will be determined today. 
</P>
<P>
 Friday's games in Bracket 2: No. 31 Mt. San Jacinto (15-15) is at No. 2 Long 
Beach (26-6), No 18 Irvine Valley (18-14) is at No. 15 Los Angeles Southwestern 
(20-7), No. 23 Rio Hondo (17-15) is at No. 10 Cuesta (22-9), and No. 14 
MiraCosta (14-14) is at No. 7 Saddleback (21-8). 
</P>
<P>
 Friday's games in Bracket 4: No. 29 Los Angeles Trade Tech (14-16) is at No. 4 
Chaffey (28-5), No. 20 San Diego Mesa (15-13) is at No. 13 College of the 
Canyons (14-16), No. 21 Bakersfield (14-18) is at No. 12 Fullerton (23-10) and 
No. 28 Oxnard (12-17) is at No. 5 Los Angeles City (25-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday's games in Bracket 1: No. 32 Los Angeles Harbor (13-16) is at No. 1 
Ventura (31-2), No. 17 Compton (18-14) is at No. 16 Rancho Santiago (20-11), 
No. 24 Santa Monica (20-10) is at No. 9 Cerritos (25-6) and No. 25 Cypress 
(15-18) is at No. 8 Imperial Valley (19-11). 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday's games in Bracket 4: No. 30 Cerro Coso (11-12) is at No. 3 Riverside 
(26-6), No. 19 Pasadena (15-15) is at No. 14 Antelope Valley (19-11), No. 22 
Glendale (15-14) is at No. 11 Southwestern (24-5) and No. 27 Orange Coast 
(13-16) is at No. 6 Moorpark (23-8). 
</P>
<P>
 Winners advance to the second round March 2. The regional finals are March 5 
and the four finalists in Southern and Northern California advance to the State 
tournament March 10-12 at UC Irvine. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
