COMMUNITY COLLEGE BASEBALL; WARD'S SINGLE IS THE KEY FOR RANCHO SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Daryle Ward had a one-out RBI single to give Rancho Santiago a 12-11 victory 
over Rio Hondo in a nonconference baseball game Tuesday in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 Ward's hit capped an impressive late-inning rally for the Dons (10-2).Rio 
Hondo scored three runs in the top of the seventh inning to take an 11-5 lead. 
But Rancho Santiago scored two in the seventh, three in the eighth and two more 
in the ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 David Mallas started the ninth-inning rally with a double and one out later, 
Matt Kastelic tripled to tie the score. Raul Gonzalez had a double, a triple 
and three RBIs also for Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 9, Palomar 3 -- Shawn Allbee (2-1) allowed two runs in six innings 
for host Golden West (6-4). Ken Phann had two hits and scored three runs for 
Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 13, San Diego Mesa 13 (10 innings, darkness) -- David Biddinger had 
a three-run home run in the ninth to tie the score for Saddleback (4-3-1). 
</P>
