<P>
THOMAS MCCARTIN; EX-TIMES MIRROR OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thomas Ronald McCartin, former publisher of the Dallas Times Herald and 
executive of Times Mirror Co., has died in Dallas.He was 59. 
</P>
<P>
 McCartin died Sunday of heart disease, hours before a fund-raising dinner he 
had organized to benefit restoration of Vatican artworks. The Vatican was a 
client of the marketing company he operated. 
</P>
<P>
 McCartin was publisher of the now-defunct Dallas paper from 1981 to 1983 when 
it was owned by Times Mirror. Under his tenure, the Times Herald won two 
Pulitzer Prizes. 
</P>
<P>
 McCartin served as president and chief executive director of Times Mirror 
National Marketing in New York. He had worked for the Washington Post and Los 
Angeles Times, and owned a weekly newspaper. 
