<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN THE LINE OF FIRE; IN THE LAST YEAR, NINE SOUTHLAND LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICERS 
HAVE BEEN SHOT TO DEATH WHILE ON DUTY. HERE IS A LOOK AT THOSE OFFICERS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 James Wayne MacDonald, 23 
</P>
<P>
 Compton Police Department, reserve officer 
</P>
<P>
 The incident: Shot execution-style on Feb. 22, 1993, after making a traffic 
stop with partner Kevin Michael Burrell. 
</P>
<P>
 Status of investigation: Suspect Regis Deon Thomas, 22, is awaiting trial. 
</P>
<P>
 Family: Single. 
</P>
<P>
 "The one thing Jimmy never doubted was that his career would involve giving to 
people, involve doing for the people," longtime friend Paul Smith, speaking at 
MacDonald's funeral. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Michael Burrell, 29 
</P>
<P>
 Compton Police Department, five-year veteran 
</P>
<P>
 The Incident: Shot execution-style on Feb. 22, 1993, after making a traffic 
stop with partner James Wayne MacDonald. 
</P>
<P>
 Status of investigation: Suspect Regis Deon Thomas, 22, is awaiting trial. 
</P>
<P>
 Family: Survived by his parents and a 3-year-old son. 
</P>
<P>
 "This church is filled with love, gratitude and pride. Kevin Burrell has been 
taken from us, but his memory will survive." Gov. Pete Wilson, addressing 
Burrell's parents. 
</P>
